WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.960
And I want to invite all of us to please turn together to the book of Ephesians.

2
00:00:05.960 --> 00:00:13.800
So if you've not been here before, we've been going through the book of Ephesians in the New Testament.

3
00:00:13.800 --> 00:00:22.200
And in the book of Ephesians, we see what it means to be in Christ and to find our identity together in him.

4
00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:29.680
And over the past couple of weeks, we've seen that in Christ we can have a new life.

5
00:00:29.680 --> 00:00:33.280
We've been given a new self.

6
00:00:33.280 --> 00:00:41.920
And that new self is characterized by true likeness and holiness because it is created in the image of God.

7
00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:44.840
It is the very likeness of Christ that has been given to us.

8
00:00:44.840 --> 00:00:47.640
We are clothed in the righteousness of Jesus.

9
00:00:47.640 --> 00:00:50.240
This is the new self.

10
00:00:50.240 --> 00:00:55.480
We're also seeing now that there's a new way of life that corresponds with that new self.

11
00:00:55.480 --> 00:00:57.320
So we've been made new in Christ.

12
00:00:57.320 --> 00:00:58.760
What does that look like in practice?

13
00:00:58.760 --> 00:01:01.200
And that's what our text is going to show us today.

14
00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:11.840
So let's read Ephesians chapter four and we're going to begin in verse 25 and read down into chapter five, verses one and two.

15
00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:14.520
It says, Therefore having put away falsehood,

16
00:01:14.520 --> 00:01:20.760
Let each one of you speak the truth with his neighbor, for we are members of one another.

17
00:01:20.760 --> 00:01:23.400
Be angry and do not sin.

18
00:01:23.400 --> 00:01:29.400
Do not let the sun go down on your anger and give no opportunity to the devil.

19
00:01:29.400 --> 00:01:37.000
Let the thief no longer steal, but rather let him labor, doing honest work with his own hands,

20
00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:41.200
so that he may have something to share with anyone in need.

21
00:01:41.200 --> 00:01:48.120
Let no corrupting talk come out of your mouths, but only such as is good for building up as fits the occasion,

22
00:01:48.120 --> 00:01:50.880
that it may give grace to those who hear.

23
00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:57.360
And do not grieve the Holy Spirit of God by whom you were sealed for the day of redemption.

24
00:01:57.360 --> 00:02:06.480
Let all bitterness and wrath and anger and clamor and slander be put away from you, along with all malice.

25
00:02:06.480 --> 00:02:13.640
Be kind to one another, tenderhearted, forgiving one another as God and Christ forgave you.

26
00:02:13.640 --> 00:02:20.920
Therefore be imitators of God as beloved children and walk in love as Christ loved us

27
00:02:20.920 --> 00:02:27.920
and gave himself up for us as a fragrant offering and sacrifice to God.

28
00:02:27.920 --> 00:02:30.920
This is the word of the Lord.

29
00:02:30.920 --> 00:02:34.040
Let's pray together, shall we?

30
00:02:34.040 --> 00:02:37.160
Lord, we want to pray now what we've just sung.

31
00:02:37.160 --> 00:02:41.440
Speak, oh Lord, as we come to you.

32
00:02:41.440 --> 00:02:48.560
Lord, I pray that as we open your word together, that we would receive it as from you.

33
00:02:48.560 --> 00:02:54.520
I pray that your spirit would open our eyes to see more of Jesus.

34
00:02:54.520 --> 00:03:01.560
And Lord, as we see more of him, Lord, I pray that we would also see even ourselves more clearly.

35
00:03:01.560 --> 00:03:06.680
Lord, as we see him and see ourselves, that it would cause us not to shy away,

36
00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:14.040
but Lord, to run to Christ and to know the grace and mercy and life that are found in him.

37
00:03:14.040 --> 00:03:17.480
We pray all of this in his name, amen.

38
00:03:17.480 --> 00:03:23.160
Well, if you were to look up a list of the greatest artists of all time,

39
00:03:23.160 --> 00:03:25.880
there'd be a few names that would pop up on pretty much every list,

40
00:03:25.880 --> 00:03:28.440
but one of them would certainly be Michelangelo.

41
00:03:28.440 --> 00:03:33.440
Now, Michelangelo, so not the Ninja Turtle in case anybody was curious,

42
00:03:33.440 --> 00:03:37.600
Michelangelo was this great artist and he did paintings.

43
00:03:37.600 --> 00:03:39.920
He was involved in architecture.

44
00:03:39.920 --> 00:03:47.600
He also wrote poetry, but his favorite art form and probably his most lasting legacy was his sculptures.

45
00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:51.880
And probably his most famous sculpture is David.

46
00:03:51.880 --> 00:03:57.640
And over a million people still go to see that sculpture every single year.

47
00:03:57.640 --> 00:04:03.440
But he once said something that gave insight as to how he approached his work as a sculptor.

48
00:04:03.440 --> 00:04:04.920
And it stuck with me.

49
00:04:04.920 --> 00:04:06.120
Now, let's know what he said.

50
00:04:06.120 --> 00:04:10.640
He said, every block of stone has a statue inside it.

51
00:04:10.640 --> 00:04:15.400
And it is the task of the sculptor to discover it.

52
00:04:15.400 --> 00:04:22.360
And then he says, I saw the angel in the marble and carved until I set him free.

53
00:04:22.360 --> 00:04:25.800
So from his perspective, as he's looking at the marble, as he's looking at the stone,

54
00:04:25.800 --> 00:04:27.680
the statue is already there.

55
00:04:27.680 --> 00:04:36.960
And it's his job to chip away at it and get in there and find that statue to kind of draw out what is already there.

56
00:04:36.960 --> 00:04:45.040
And like the sculptures trapped in the marble, what we're seeing about the new self is that it is already there.

57
00:04:45.040 --> 00:04:52.160
If you have put off the old self and put on the new self, you have already been recreated in the image of God.

58
00:04:52.160 --> 00:04:58.000
You've been given the righteousness and holiness of Jesus.

59
00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:02.880
And yet that likeness must be brought out.

60
00:05:02.880 --> 00:05:08.120
It takes a lifetime of sculpting for that to be seen.

61
00:05:08.120 --> 00:05:14.160
So to put this in theological terms, sometimes this is referred to like those two things being true at the same time as

62
00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:18.840
positional sanctification and progressive sanctification.

63
00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:21.080
So hold that thought with me for a second.

64
00:05:21.080 --> 00:05:25.000
So positional sanctification says this is your position.

65
00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:32.080
Like you are in Christ, you are already sanctified, you are already set apart when God sees you,

66
00:05:32.080 --> 00:05:37.560
he sees you in the very righteousness of his son, Jesus.

67
00:05:37.560 --> 00:05:39.200
That's already true of you.

68
00:05:39.200 --> 00:05:40.440
That's your position.

69
00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:42.400
But here's the progression.

70
00:05:42.400 --> 00:05:49.320
At the same time, you are also called to be sanctified, to live a holy life.

71
00:05:49.360 --> 00:05:52.240
And that is a progressive and ongoing thing.

72
00:05:52.240 --> 00:05:59.040
It's the fruit of Christ's righteousness being born in your life.

73
00:05:59.040 --> 00:06:01.720
And so that happens over a lifetime.

74
00:06:01.720 --> 00:06:08.000
And so basically you have this ongoing integration between the new self and our way of lives,

75
00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.280
the way of life that corresponds with that new self.

76
00:06:12.280 --> 00:06:13.680
But there's wonderful news.

77
00:06:13.680 --> 00:06:18.320
And here's the wonderful news is that the master sculptor is the one who is bringing this about.

